{{wikipedia|Alexander (disambiguation)}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin '''Alexander''', Romanization of Greek [[Αλέξανδρος]] (Aléxandros), compounded from [[αλέξω]] (alexo = "to [[defend]]") and [[ανδρός]] (andros), genitive of [[ανήρ]] (anér = "[[man]]"): ''defender of men''.

===Proper noun===
'''Alexander''' (''plural:'' [[Alexanders]])

# A male [[given name]].
#often refers to [[Wikipedia:Alexander the Great|Alexander the Great]].
